Nguyễn Hà My is an Intern/Fresher Software Engineer with no commercial experience, demonstrating a strong academic foundation and practical project-based skills. Their core expertise lies in applying various Design Patterns, including Singleton, Factory, Strategy, Observer, Command, Decorator, Adapter, Template, State, and Builder, to achieve Clean Architecture. They are proficient in developing RESTful APIs and implementing WebSocket for real-time communication, alongside a solid understanding of Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) and CRUD Operations. Through personal projects, Nguyễn Hà My has engineered a mobile English learning application leveraging Java, XML, and Firebase for real-time data and authentication, a responsive electronic components management website utilizing Tailwind CSS, Express.js, JWT, and MongoDB, and a cross-platform e-commerce application built with Dart, Flutter, Python, Firebase, and WebSocket, featuring real-time communication. Additional experience includes a web-based high school student management platform developed using ReactJS, Node.js, and MongoDB. They also hold a certification in Agile Development and the Scrum Framework.
Technically, Nguyễn Hà My is proficient across multiple programming languages including Java, Python, Dart, C#, C, and JavaScript. Their framework and library expertise spans web development with Express.js, Bootstrap, HTML, CSS, Tailwind CSS, ReactJS, and Node.js, as well as cross-platform mobile development with Flutter and UI design using XML. Database management skills include SQL Server, MongoDB, Firebase, and Appwrite. In terms of DevOps and cloud exposure, they have experience with AWS, Railway, Docker, and Firebase, while utilizing Git, GitHub, GitLab for version control and Postman for API testing. Nguyễn Hà My is currently pursuing a Bachelor's degree in Information Technology - Software Engineering from Ton Duc Thang University, maintaining a high GPA of 8.68, and possesses Intermediate English proficiency (APTIS Level B1 CEFR).